text.section:
The contents of a case record may be disclosed:
if the record is necessary to ensure proper medical treatment, to a provider of medical services to the inmate;
to the inmate's attorney;
to a person authorized by a court order;
to a person expressly authorized by law;
to a judge of a State court;
to a State's Attorney;
to an employee of any State unit or a federal or local law enforcement unit, if disclosure is in furtherance of the employee's lawful duties; and
on written request, to a person who has written authorization for the disclosure from the inmate.
